<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About Us </title>

</head>

<body>
    <h1>About Us</h1>

    <div class="team-members">
        <div class="team-member" id="akash">
            <h2>Akash Mishra</h2>
            <p>Passionate about surfing and web development. Akash loves to ride the waves both on the ocean and in the coding world.</p>
            <img src="/images/akash.jpg" alt="Akash">
            <div class="contributions" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <h3 style="font-size: 16px;">Contributions</h3>
                <p>Akash contributed to this project by working on the background theme of the website and the About Us page.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member" id="andrew">
            <h2>Andrew Scott</h2>
            <p>Andrew has a background in Finance and Analytics and has been honing his programming and data technical skills. In his free time, Andrew enjoys surfing and any and all water related sports.</p>
            <img src="/images/andrew.jpg" alt="Andrew">
            <div class="contributions" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <h3 style="font-size: 16px;">Contributions</h3>
                <p>Andrew worked on setting up the chart and the homepage and is responsible for the finding of the data API.</p>   
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="team-member" id="varsha">
            <h2>Varsha Disawal</h2>
            <p>Surfing and coding go hand in hand for Varsha. She brings creativity to the team, both on the waves and in designing websites.</p>
            <img src="/images/varsha.jpg" alt="Varsha">
            <div class="contributions" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <h3 style="font-size: 16px;">Contributions</h3>
                <p>Varsha made significant contributions to the project's overall design and website development.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="data-model">
        <div class="data-model-container">
            <h2 class="data-model-heading">Data Model</h2>
            <p>
                Our website revolves around three main tables in the data model: Wind, Waves, and Location. 
                Data is sourced from a publically available weather API from Windy.com. A sample API endpoint is shown below.
            </p>
            <a href="https://api.windy.com/point-forecast/docs">POST https://api.windy.com/api/point-forecast/v2</a>

            <p>
                    {<br />
                    "lat": 49.809,<br />
                    "lon": 16.787,<br />
                    "model": "gfs",<br />
                    "parameters": ["wind", "dewpoint", "rh", "pressure"],<br />
                    "levels": ["surface", "800h", "300h"],<br />
                    "key": "abcd123"<br />
                    }</p>

        </div>
        <img src="/images/erd_DIS.png" alt="Data Model">
    </div>

    <div class="github-link">
        <button onclick="window.open('https://github.com/saltyscott0521/DIS_HTML', '_blank')">Checkout GitHub Repo</button>
    </div>

    <script>
        // JavaScript for smooth transitions -
        document.body.addEventListener('mouseover', () => {
            document.body.style.background = 'url("~/wwwroot/images/surf.jpg") no-repeat center center fixed';
            document.body.style.backgroundSize = 'cover';
        });

        document.body.addEventListener('mouseout', () => {
            document.body.style.background = 'url("~/wwwroot/images/surf.jpg") no-repeat center center fixed';
            document.body.style.backgroundSize = 'cover';
        });
    </script>

</body>
</html>
